[Plums chattering softly]

243
00:11:45.037 --> 00:11:48.290
Mrs. Judd has graciously
opened her home to us.

244
00:11:48.374 --> 00:11:52.503
This is an opportunity to learn.
especially for you. Green girls.

245
00:11:58.676 --> 00:12:00.302
I liked going to the zoo.

246
00:12:00.386 --> 00:12:02.471
Well. we're not 10 anymore. Hulda.

247
00:12:03.556 --> 00:12:06.183
It'll be fun. We get to see Penny.

248
00:12:06.267 --> 00:12:07.560
Mrs. Judd.

249
00:12:07.643 --> 00:12:09.019
Mrs. Commander Judd.

250
00:12:10.146 --> 00:12:11.439
She's still Penny.

251
00:12:14.775 --> 00:12:16.694
Lots of adults like going
to the zoo. you know.

252
00:12:19.071 --> 00:12:21.699
Heads up. Dirty girl coming.

253
00:12:21.782 --> 00:12:24.493
[♪ music continues]

254
00:12:24.577 --> 00:12:26.162
Blessed be the fruit.

255
00:12:26.662 --> 00:12:28.205
May the Lord open.

256
00:12:34.003 --> 00:12:35.254
We've been sent fine weather.

257
00:12:35.337 --> 00:12:37.339
Which we already received with joy.

258
00:12:38.132 --> 00:12:42.636
Single-file line.
Punctuality requires order.

259
00:12:46.348 --> 00:12:49.059
[♪ light music playing]

260
00:12:51.437 --> 00:12:53.439
[bus engine idling]

261
00:12:58.277 --> 00:13:00.863
[♪ light music continues playing]

262
00:13:02.823 --> 00:13:04.408
Have a blessed day. Miss Agnes.

263
00:13:05.451 --> 00:13:06.827
May the Lord open.

264
00:13:10.790 --> 00:13:13.501
[Daisy] <i>I wasn't surprised</i>
<i>she wanted to bone him.</i>

265
00:13:13.959 --> 00:13:15.669
<i>I mean. look at him.</i>

266
00:13:25.179 --> 00:13:27.181
[engines rumbling]

267
00:13:29.016 --> 00:13:30.226
[dog barking]

268
00:13:31.018 --> 00:13:33.854
[♪ light music continues]

269
00:14:02.967 --> 00:14:05.261
[Daisy] <i>I used to stare</i>
<i>at Justin like that.</i>

270
00:14:08.138 --> 00:14:09.765
<i>Every inch of him.</i>

271
00:14:12.643 --> 00:14:14.270
That's your Guardian. right?

272
00:14:16.397 --> 00:14:17.940
You're being a slut.

273
00:14:18.023 --> 00:14:19.066
What?

274
00:14:19.149 --> 00:14:21.360
Lusting after him so openly.

275
00:14:22.444 --> 00:14:23.863
It's a gateway to Hell.

276
00:14:24.572 --> 00:14:26.657
I pray they teach you Pearls
better than that.

277
00:14:27.366 --> 00:14:30.828
[Daisy] <i>Yeah. okay. I'm the slut?</i>

278
00:14:33.539 --> 00:14:35.541
Apologies. Miss Agnes.

279
00:14:39.336 --> 00:14:41.171
[driver] Chapin. something ahead.

280
00:14:43.716 --> 00:14:45.718
[♪ tense music playing]

281
00:14:45.801 --> 00:14:48.220
-[Daisy] What's going on?
-[Agnes] I don't know.

282
00:14:52.474 --> 00:14:54.101
[Plum girl 1] What's happening?

283
00:14:54.184 --> 00:14:55.811
[Garth] Check the mirror.

284
00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:58.856
-Do you know what's going on?
-[♪ tense music continues]

285
00:14:58.939 --> 00:15:00.357
[Garth] I-I can't tell yet.

286
00:15:00.441 --> 00:15:01.984
[Plum girl 2] What's he doing?

287
00:15:02.067 --> 00:15:03.694
[Garth] They're armed. shooters.

288
00:15:03.777 --> 00:15:05.779
[panicked murmuring]

289
00:15:07.489 --> 00:15:09.325
[truck accelerating]

290
00:15:11.035 --> 00:15:14.455
-[Garth] We're getting boxed in.
-[tires screeching. vehicles crashing]

291
00:15:14.538 --> 00:15:17.166
[all screaming]

292
00:15:17.249 --> 00:15:20.002
We're under attack! We need backup.
Repeat: we are under attack.

293
00:15:20.085 --> 00:15:21.712
Send immediate backup.

294
00:15:21.795 --> 00:15:24.423
-[tires screeching]
-[screaming continues]

295
00:15:27.426 --> 00:15:28.636
[indistinct shouting]

296
00:15:28.719 --> 00:15:30.930
-[Daisy] Agnes! Get down!
-[gunfire]

297
00:15:33.098 --> 00:15:34.516
-[gunfire continues]
-[screaming. shouting]

298
00:15:34.600 --> 00:15:36.602
[Aunt] Everybody stay down!

299
00:15:36.685 --> 00:15:40.147
May the Lord guard me.
May Thy might save me.

300
00:15:40.230 --> 00:15:42.441
[Garth] Okay. let's go. Get up! Now!

301
00:15:43.317 --> 00:15:45.945
[Plums screaming. whimpering]

302
00:15:47.905 --> 00:15:49.865
Everyone off the bus now!

303
00:15:49.949 --> 00:15:53.535
Let's go now! Move. in there! Go. go!

304
00:15:53.619 --> 00:15:55.704
-[Guardian 1] Move. move!
-[Plums screaming]

305
00:15:55.788 --> 00:15:57.414
[Guardian 2]
Protect the Plums! Get 'em in there!

306
00:15:57.498 --> 00:15:59.917
-Agnes. come on. let's go!
-[Guardian 3] Go. go. go!

307
00:16:00.751 --> 00:16:04.213
-Turn right! The perps are down.
-In there. go. Heads down.

308
00:16:04.296 --> 00:16:05.506
Get in the shop.

309
00:16:06.590 --> 00:16:08.008
Stay down!

310
00:16:08.676 --> 00:16:10.302
Move. move. come on! Let's go!

311
00:16:10.386 --> 00:16:13.597
-[♪ dramatic music playing]
-[helicopter whirring]

312
00:16:15.933 --> 00:16:17.434
[gasping]

313
00:16:23.774 --> 00:16:27.903
[♪ dramatic music playing]

314
00:16:27.987 --> 00:16:29.196
[♪ music fades out]

315
00:16:45.212 --> 00:16:46.714
[gasps. whimpers]

316
00:16:46.797 --> 00:16:49.008
[♪ somber music playing]

317
00:16:51.218 --> 00:16:52.594
[exhales sharply]

318
00:16:52.678 --> 00:16:55.097
[sobbing softly]

319
00:16:57.516 --> 00:16:58.517
[sniffles]

320
00:17:00.227 --> 00:17:01.437
That's them.

321
00:17:07.443 --> 00:17:08.652
[exhales]

322
00:17:10.779 --> 00:17:11.780
[sniffles]

323
00:17:17.244 --> 00:17:19.246
[♪ somber music fades]

324
00:17:19.329 --> 00:17:22.541
-[approaching footsteps]
-[phones ringing]

325
00:17:24.585 --> 00:17:28.422
Hi. I'm Tim. I'm with Social Services.

326
00:17:28.505 --> 00:17:31.258
-[hospital PA announcement]
-Sorry for your loss.

327
00:17:31.341 --> 00:17:32.593
[Daisy] Okay.

328
00:17:32.676 --> 00:17:34.386
[hospital phone ringing]

329
00:17:34.470 --> 00:17:36.555
I'm sorry. I'm still really stoned.

330
00:17:36.638 --> 00:17:37.848
That's fine.

331
00:17:39.141 --> 00:17:40.309
It's tea.

332
00:17:42.311 --> 00:17:43.896
Do you want a soda?

333
00:17:43.979 --> 00:17:47.191
I need my phone.
The police took it.

334
00:17:47.274 --> 00:17:48.901
Is there anyone I can call for you?

335
00:17:48.984 --> 00:17:50.194
Some family maybe?

336
00:17:50.277 --> 00:17:52.071
I just want my phone.

337
00:17:52.154 --> 00:17:54.698
[Tim] Sure. We can sort
through all that together.

338
00:17:54.782 --> 00:17:56.784
But we don't have to do that here.

339
00:17:57.785 --> 00:18:00.788
I'll go sign you out real quick.
and then we'll leave.

340
00:18:03.832 --> 00:18:05.667
Drink your tea. Don't move.

341
00:18:14.968 --> 00:18:17.596
[hospital PA announcement]

342
00:18:21.016 --> 00:18:23.644
[♪ intriguing music playing]

343
00:18:27.731 --> 00:18:28.941
[sighs]

344
00:18:30.359 --> 00:18:32.194
Daisy?

345
00:18:33.153 --> 00:18:35.697
Hi. I need you to come with me.

346
00:18:35.781 --> 00:18:37.741
Are you with Social Services. too?

347
00:18:37.825 --> 00:18:39.243
There's been a change of plan.

348
00:18:41.161 --> 00:18:43.163
I need my phone.
The other guy was getting it.

349
00:18:43.247 --> 00:18:45.958
-There was another guy?
-Yeah. he gave me this tea.

350
00:18:48.001 --> 00:18:50.003
-What are you doing?
-Come on.

351
00:18:50.087 --> 00:18:51.588
Okay. I'm going back for my stuff.

352
00:18:51.672 --> 00:18:53.215
-No.
-No. why?

353
00:18:53.298 --> 00:18:55.384
Because you're in danger.
I need to get you out of here.

354
00:18:55.467 --> 00:18:57.344
[Daisy] What? In danger from what?

355
00:18:57.427 --> 00:18:59.221
-Danger from what?
-[shushes]

356
00:18:59.304 --> 00:19:00.305
Come on.

357
00:19:01.974 --> 00:19:04.977
-[people chattering]
-[phones ringing]

358
00:19:10.524 --> 00:19:12.151
Go. go. go. go.

359
00:19:13.152 --> 00:19:14.278
[door shuts]

360
00:19:14.361 --> 00:19:16.697
You're in danger from the people
who killed your parents.

361
00:19:16.780 --> 00:19:18.365
The people who robbed the store?

362
00:19:18.448 --> 00:19:20.951
It wasn't a robbery.
Neil and Melanie were murdered.

363
00:19:21.034 --> 00:19:23.453
They were killed and now you're in danger.

364
00:19:23.537 --> 00:19:25.372
Pardon fucking me. what?

365
00:19:25.455 --> 00:19:27.291
You're not from Social Services?

366
00:19:27.374 --> 00:19:30.210
No. I'm not. That guy isn't
from Social Services either.

367
00:19:30.836 --> 00:19:33.172
Look. Daisy. I'm sorry.

368
00:19:33.255 --> 00:19:34.631
No one should have to go through this.

369
00:19:34.715 --> 00:19:36.633
but I need you to trust me.

370
00:19:36.717 --> 00:19:38.343
Who are you?

371
00:19:39.928 --> 00:19:42.097
[door opening]

372
00:19:42.181 --> 00:19:43.557
[whispering] Come on.

373
00:19:43.640 --> 00:19:46.643
-[hospital phone ringing]
-[people chattering]

374
00:19:55.235 --> 00:19:57.070
[♪ dramatic music playing]

375
00:19:57.154 --> 00:19:58.363
[whispering] Shit.

376
00:20:07.039 --> 00:20:09.875
[indistinct police radio chatter]

377
00:20:11.919 --> 00:20:13.921
I was a friend of your parents.

378
00:20:20.469 --> 00:20:22.387
You've been to the store.

379
00:20:22.471 --> 00:20:23.889
Many times.

380
00:20:25.098 --> 00:20:28.101
[♪ intriguing music playing]

381
00:20:39.154 --> 00:20:40.572
What's your name?

382
00:20:48.830 --> 00:20:49.915
June.

383
00:20:50.499 --> 00:20:52.209
My name is June.

384
00:20:54.044 --> 00:20:56.046
Daisy. I need you to come with me.

385
00:20:58.507 --> 00:21:02.511
Okay. But June. listen.
I'm still pretty stoned.

386
00:21:02.594 --> 00:21:03.804
Right.

387
00:21:04.638 --> 00:21:06.848
Okay. fine. Uh. we'll deal with that.

388
00:21:07.724 --> 00:21:10.560
Yeah. come on.
Let's get you somewhere safe.

389
00:21:19.444 --> 00:21:22.155
[helicopter whirring]

390
00:21:22.239 --> 00:21:26.159
[people chattering]

391
00:21:26.660 --> 00:21:29.705
Thank you... for shielding me.

392
00:21:32.499 --> 00:21:34.710
God found a way to make me useful.

393
00:21:34.793 --> 00:21:36.795
[indistinct chatter]

394
00:21:36.878 --> 00:21:40.716
[siren wailing]

395
00:21:40.799 --> 00:21:43.302
Honestly. I was terrified.

396
00:21:44.469 --> 00:21:46.096
Me too.

397
00:21:46.179 --> 00:21:48.515
[footsteps approaching]

398
00:21:49.057 --> 00:21:51.393
Hulda. Does it hurt?

399
00:21:51.476 --> 00:21:53.979
They said that it would heal. praise be.

400
00:21:55.105 --> 00:21:56.523
[Shunammite] Minimal scarring.

401
00:21:56.606 --> 00:21:59.318
Aunt Vidala's arm is broken.

402
00:22:00.110 --> 00:22:01.528
[girl] It hurts.

403
00:22:01.611 --> 00:22:03.530
May He bring her comfort.

404
00:22:07.993 --> 00:22:09.536
Do they know who did it?

405
00:22:09.619 --> 00:22:11.538
[scoffs] Mayday.

406
00:22:11.621 --> 00:22:12.748
[Agnes] Godless animals.

407
00:22:12.831 --> 00:22:15.542
[Becka] They're the terrible people
we're enemies with.

408
00:22:15.625 --> 00:22:17.085
They hate us.

409
00:22:18.670 --> 00:22:23.175
Hulda... tell them what else you saw.

410
00:22:23.258 --> 00:22:25.260
[people chattering quietly]

411
00:22:28.180 --> 00:22:30.474
They were bandaging a Guardian.

412
00:22:30.557 --> 00:22:32.225
[whispering] His shirt was lifted

413
00:22:32.309 --> 00:22:34.728
and there was hair on his stomach.

414
00:22:35.312 --> 00:22:36.480
All over.

415
00:22:38.732 --> 00:22:40.359
What do you mean?

416
00:22:40.442 --> 00:22:42.069
It was-- It was short and stubbly.

417
00:22:42.152 --> 00:22:44.696
Almost like when my dad
grows his beard out.

418
00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:46.406
That's repulsive.

419
00:22:46.948 --> 00:22:48.867
[breathy] Yeah. it is.

420
00:22:48.950 --> 00:22:50.702
Do all men have it?

421
00:22:54.581 --> 00:22:56.041
Most men do.

422
00:22:57.542 --> 00:22:59.544
Most grown men.

423
00:23:01.671 --> 00:23:02.964
It depends. I think.

424
00:23:03.090 --> 00:23:04.633
On what?

425
00:23:04.716 --> 00:23:06.343
[whispering] Godliness?

426
00:23:07.010 --> 00:23:08.220
Genetics.

427
00:23:09.513 --> 00:23:11.014
One of God's mysteries.

428
00:23:13.475 --> 00:23:15.310
How would you know?

429
00:23:15.936 --> 00:23:18.146
Because in Toronto.

430
00:23:18.230 --> 00:23:21.566
I had sex with thousands of men.

431
00:23:23.402 --> 00:23:26.321
A real statistical cross-section.

432
00:23:27.406 --> 00:23:29.032
You probably did.

433
00:23:31.410 --> 00:23:33.620
I used to go to the beach.

434
00:23:33.703 --> 00:23:35.539
like everyone else.

435
00:23:37.124 --> 00:23:38.542
You saw bodies.

436
00:23:38.625 --> 00:23:40.252
Men would go shirtless.

437
00:23:41.336 --> 00:23:43.922
And the hair...

438
00:23:44.005 --> 00:23:47.008
Well. it keeps going.

439
00:23:48.635 --> 00:23:49.636
Lower.

440
00:23:49.719 --> 00:23:51.471
[Becka] Oh. my God.

441
00:23:52.139 --> 00:23:54.141
Oh God. protect us.

442
00:23:54.224 --> 00:23:56.101
I wonder which one
of the Commanders has it.

443
00:23:56.184 --> 00:23:57.561
Shu!

444
00:23:57.644 --> 00:23:58.812
Shu!

445
00:23:58.895 --> 00:24:00.897
[group giggling quietly]

446
00:24:09.573 --> 00:24:11.283
[water running]

447
00:24:21.501 --> 00:24:22.919
[water stops]

448
00:24:23.003 --> 00:24:24.212
[exhales]

449
00:24:30.844 --> 00:24:32.053
[sighs]

450
00:24:39.352 --> 00:24:41.396
Is your head any clearer?

451
00:24:42.939 --> 00:24:44.441
You wanna eat something?

452
00:24:44.524 --> 00:24:46.109
Can I borrow your phone?

453
00:24:46.193 --> 00:24:49.029
I need to call my boyfriend.
He's gonna be. like. worried.

454
00:24:50.071 --> 00:24:52.699
Why don't you eat something.
and then we can talk about it?

455
00:24:52.782 --> 00:24:56.578
Or let me call my boyfriend.
and then I'll eat something.

456
00:24:56.661 --> 00:24:58.330
We're not negotiating.

457
00:25:02.834 --> 00:25:05.253
Why would anyone murder my parents?

458
00:25:07.130 --> 00:25:09.090
It was Gilead.

459
00:25:09.174 --> 00:25:10.509
Agents from Gilead.

460
00:25:10.592 --> 00:25:11.927
[scoffs]

461
00:25:12.010 --> 00:25:14.638
Agents from Gilead killed my parents?

462
00:25:14.721 --> 00:25:15.931
Mm-hmm.

463
00:25:16.681 --> 00:25:19.142
Why in the fucking world
would that be true?

464
00:25:28.568 --> 00:25:30.487
Do you know what Mayday is?

465
00:25:30.570 --> 00:25:31.571
Sure.

466
00:25:31.655 --> 00:25:33.323
Learned about them in school.

467
00:25:34.324 --> 00:25:35.534
Ah.

468
00:25:36.076 --> 00:25:38.078
Your parents were working with Mayday.

469
00:25:38.828 --> 00:25:40.455
They were working with me.

470
00:25:40.539 --> 00:25:43.124
My parents are arms smugglers
or something?

471
00:25:44.918 --> 00:25:46.378
They run a vintage store.

472
00:25:46.461 --> 00:25:49.130
My dad doesn't even know
how to use Find My Friends.

473
00:25:49.214 --> 00:25:53.051
They are the least spy people
in the universe.

474
00:25:54.844 --> 00:25:57.264
There are things you don't know
about them. Daisy.

475
00:25:57.347 --> 00:25:59.057
Are you Mayday too?

476
00:26:02.477 --> 00:26:05.230
They would have told me if they
were involved in something like that.

477
00:26:05.313 --> 00:26:08.942
Yeah. they were planning to.
It's not that easy.

478
00:26:09.025 --> 00:26:11.027
Telling you would put you
in a lot of danger.

479
00:26:11.111 --> 00:26:13.488
[sighs] This is ridiculous.

480
00:26:13.572 --> 00:26:15.574
I wanna call my boyfriend.

481
00:26:15.657 --> 00:26:17.742
[June sighs heavily]

482
00:26:17.826 --> 00:26:21.705
I need a few hours to arrange
to get you out of the city safely.

483
00:26:21.788 --> 00:26:23.790
He's gonna find out what happened.

484
00:26:24.416 --> 00:26:26.293
And he's gonna think I'm fucking dead.

485
00:26:26.376 --> 00:26:27.419
-Daisy--
-Okay?

486
00:26:27.502 --> 00:26:29.129
So I need to talk to him.

487
00:26:33.883 --> 00:26:35.385
[June sighs]

488
00:26:36.052 --> 00:26:38.972
That part of your life is over.

489
00:26:40.348 --> 00:26:41.558
Okay?

490
00:26:42.475 --> 00:26:44.686
And I'm sorry all this has happened.

491
00:26:46.146 --> 00:26:49.149
I know what it's like to have
everything change all at once.

492
00:26:54.446 --> 00:26:55.947
Can I borrow your phone?

493
00:26:56.031 --> 00:26:58.033
No. Daisy.

494
00:26:59.618 --> 00:27:00.619
You can't.

495
00:27:01.620 --> 00:27:04.247
I need to arrange my parents' funeral.

496
00:27:05.123 --> 00:27:07.751
Can I please use your phone to do that?

497
00:27:09.169 --> 00:27:11.171
[sighs]

498
00:27:11.838 --> 00:27:14.257
No. No. it's too dangerous.

499
00:27:20.472 --> 00:27:22.098
I think you should eat something.

500
00:27:22.891 --> 00:27:24.517
[Daisy sighs heavily]

501
00:27:24.601 --> 00:27:26.019
I'm not hungry.

502
00:27:31.983 --> 00:27:33.276
[door slams shut]

503
00:27:58.885 --> 00:28:00.720
[distant traffic humming]

504
00:28:02.514 --> 00:28:03.723
[door closes]

505
00:28:11.147 --> 00:28:13.149
[crickets chirping]

506
00:28:33.628 --> 00:28:35.463
[truck hood creaking]

507
00:28:45.807 --> 00:28:47.016
[whispers] Justin!

508
00:28:49.519 --> 00:28:51.521
[metal trellis squeaking]

509
00:28:54.107 --> 00:28:56.526
Justin. [panting]

510
00:28:58.445 --> 00:29:02.282
-Justin! Justin!
-Holy shit!

511
00:29:03.241 --> 00:29:04.659
Shh!

512
00:29:04.743 --> 00:29:06.536
[grunting]

513
00:29:06.619 --> 00:29:08.830
[both panting]

514
00:29:08.913 --> 00:29:11.332
Are you okay?
Babe. where the fuck have you been?!

515
00:29:11.416 --> 00:29:15.378
[panting] I missed you so much.

516
00:29:15.462 --> 00:29:16.880
[stammering] The police
have been looking for you.

517
00:29:16.963 --> 00:29:18.339
I've been freaking out.

518
00:29:18.423 --> 00:29:21.676
And your parents. oh. my God.
Fuck. Like. what happened?

519
00:29:21.760 --> 00:29:23.386
I'll explain everything.

520
00:29:23.470 --> 00:29:24.721
[both breathing heavily]

521
00:29:24.804 --> 00:29:27.766
I just need you to. like.
hug me or something first.

522
00:29:27.849 --> 00:29:29.934
-Yeah. Yeah. hey.
-Please. please.

523
00:29:30.018 --> 00:29:32.979
-Okay. It's okay. It's okay. Hey.
-[softly crying]

524
00:29:33.062 --> 00:29:36.316
-Come here.
-[Daisy whimpering. crying]

525
00:29:36.399 --> 00:29:39.027
It's okay. I got you.

526
00:29:40.111 --> 00:29:41.529
I have you.

527
00:29:43.114 --> 00:29:45.533
-[continues crying]
-[softly] Oh. hey.

528
00:29:45.617 --> 00:29:48.620
[♪ somber music playing]

529
00:29:51.915 --> 00:29:53.917
[Daisy panting]

530
00:30:00.840 --> 00:30:02.842
[breathing softly]

531
00:30:19.234 --> 00:30:20.401
[kiss smacking]

532
00:30:33.832 --> 00:30:37.836
Hey. Whoa. What are you d--

533
00:30:38.711 --> 00:30:40.129
Right now?

534
00:30:42.549 --> 00:30:45.176
[whispering] I just need
to feel normal again.

535
00:30:45.260 --> 00:30:46.469
Please.

536
00:30:47.095 --> 00:30:48.513
[whispering] Okay.

537
00:30:51.099 --> 00:30:53.101
[kiss smacking]

538
00:30:57.605 --> 00:31:00.233
[both breathing heavily]

539
00:31:01.651 --> 00:31:03.653
♪♪

540
00:31:19.502 --> 00:31:21.504
[♪ music fades out]

541
00:31:21.588 --> 00:31:23.006
[sighs]

542
00:31:27.135 --> 00:31:29.554
[Daisy breathes deeply]

543
00:31:37.854 --> 00:31:39.689
You need to go to the police.

544
00:31:41.399 --> 00:31:43.902
-'Kay. let me talk to my parents.
-No.

545
00:31:45.194 --> 00:31:46.821
I already explained it to you.

546
00:31:48.698 --> 00:31:51.701
Can you really trust that woman?
I mean. Mayday spies?

547
00:31:52.619 --> 00:31:55.830
Your-- Your mom couldn't even
remember her phone passcode.

548
00:31:56.456 --> 00:31:58.458
Okay? I-- I mean. come on.

549
00:31:59.459 --> 00:32:02.086
You're grieving. Of course you are.

550
00:32:03.421 --> 00:32:04.631
But it's messing with your head.

551
00:32:04.714 --> 00:32:08.343
making you believe all this crazy shit.

552
00:32:11.679 --> 00:32:13.681
[distant dog barking]

553
00:32:15.642 --> 00:32:17.268
Let's run away.

554
00:32:19.479 --> 00:32:22.690
I'm serious. I trust you. I know that.

555
00:32:24.484 --> 00:32:27.320
[breathing shakily]
We could go somewhere.

556
00:32:28.279 --> 00:32:30.281
We could get jobs.

557
00:32:30.365 --> 00:32:31.991
Sell all our shit.

558
00:32:34.035 --> 00:32:35.662
[chuckling]

559
00:32:39.165 --> 00:32:40.792
[whispering] Why is that so funny?

560
00:32:43.503 --> 00:32:46.339
You're freaking out. And I get that. okay?

561
00:32:46.422 --> 00:32:48.132
I really do.

562
00:32:48.216 --> 00:32:52.845
But... Daisy. we can't just run away.

563
00:32:54.097 --> 00:32:56.099
[Daisy softly crying]

564
00:32:57.976 --> 00:33:00.645
[♪ soft. dramatic music playing]

565
00:33:01.646 --> 00:33:03.564
[whispering] I'm sorry.

566
00:33:03.648 --> 00:33:05.858
-[Daisy sniffles]
-[Justin sighs]

567
00:33:08.319 --> 00:33:10.738
Gonna wake up my parents. okay?
We'll talk to them. step one.

568
00:33:10.822 --> 00:33:14.242
-No. Justin--
-It's gonna be okay. I promise.

569
00:33:16.119 --> 00:33:18.746
[Daisy]
<i>It wasn't gonna be okay. though.</i>

570
00:33:18.830 --> 00:33:22.750
<i>My parents were dead.</i>
<i>It didn't matter what I did.</i>

571
00:33:22.834 --> 00:33:24.836
♪♪

572
00:33:27.839 --> 00:33:29.257
<i>June was right.</i>

573
00:33:30.550 --> 00:33:32.969
<i>This part of my life was over.</i>

574
00:33:50.945 --> 00:33:52.572
[sniffling]

575
00:34:00.788 --> 00:34:02.206
[dog barking]

576
00:34:04.083 --> 00:34:05.710
[sniffling]

577
00:34:12.425 --> 00:34:14.427
[♪ solemn music playing]

578
00:34:16.471 --> 00:34:18.473
[panting]

579
00:34:23.269 --> 00:34:24.896
Let me help you.

580
00:34:26.939 --> 00:34:28.357
Why?

581
00:34:29.108 --> 00:34:31.110
'Cause I know how you're feeling.

582
00:34:32.528 --> 00:34:34.530
[♪ solemn music continues]

583
00:34:55.426 --> 00:34:57.053
[sighs deeply]

584
00:34:57.136 --> 00:34:59.138
Okay. come on. Let's go.

585
00:35:11.359 --> 00:35:14.237
[helicopter whirring]

586
00:35:14.320 --> 00:35:16.739
[girl] Whoa. look at this place.

587
00:35:16.823 --> 00:35:18.825
[girls murmuring]

588
00:35:23.454 --> 00:35:25.456
[Daisy]
<i>It had been a week since the bus attack.</i>

589
00:35:25.540 --> 00:35:29.752
-[indistinct radio chatter]
<i>-Godly girls bounce back so quickly.</i>

590
00:35:31.420 --> 00:35:34.841
Remember. we are Mrs. Judd's guests.

591
00:35:34.924 --> 00:35:36.968
And how do guests show respect?

592
00:35:37.051 --> 00:35:39.679
With good posture.
Straighten up. Constance.

593
00:35:39.762 --> 00:35:41.764
[birds chirping]

594
00:35:52.608 --> 00:35:54.026
Blessed day. Aunt Vidala.

595
00:35:55.653 --> 00:35:56.654
[chuckles]

596
00:35:56.737 --> 00:35:58.030
-Hey!
-[both giggling]

597
00:35:58.114 --> 00:35:59.115
Hi!

598
00:35:59.198 --> 00:36:01.909
I am so happy to see you all.

599
00:36:01.993 --> 00:36:03.202
-Oh. Penny.
-Hi.

600
00:36:03.286 --> 00:36:04.787
This is Daisy.

601
00:36:04.871 --> 00:36:06.539
-Hi.
-Hi. Daisy.

602
00:36:06.622 --> 00:36:08.583
-Nice to meet you.
-Hi.

603
00:36:08.666 --> 00:36:10.877
I can't believe
what you've all been through.

604
00:36:11.669 --> 00:36:15.339
These gifts. You're all too much.
This is too much.

605
00:36:15.423 --> 00:36:19.010
-Penny. your house is so...
-Come in.

606
00:36:19.093 --> 00:36:20.094
Look at this place!

607
00:36:20.178 --> 00:36:21.596
Come in! Come in!

608
00:36:26.893 --> 00:36:27.894
Alright.

609
00:36:28.728 --> 00:36:29.937
Can I show you around?

610
00:36:30.021 --> 00:36:32.023
-[Plums] Yes!
-[soft laughter]

611
00:36:38.779 --> 00:36:39.989
[sighs]

612
00:36:40.698 --> 00:36:41.699
Martha!

613
00:36:41.782 --> 00:36:44.160
[Penny] So. of course.
I chose pink for the living room.

614
00:36:44.243 --> 00:36:46.245
-[all laughing]
-Um. it all matches so well.

615
00:36:46.329 --> 00:36:48.122
I love the way it came together.
The flowers.

616
00:36:48.206 --> 00:36:52.210
The only thing is this painting
that. um. Michael chose.

617
00:36:53.127 --> 00:36:55.129
We're gonna-- We're gonna
swap it for something else.

618
00:36:55.213 --> 00:36:56.214
[all laughing]

619
00:36:56.297 --> 00:36:57.757
Let me show you the kitchen. Come on.

620
00:36:57.840 --> 00:36:59.884
[♪ "Cherry on Top" by Tabitha Meeks
and Teddy Morgan playing]

621
00:36:59.967 --> 00:37:02.386
<i>♪ Shiny penny on Azalea Street ♪</i>

622
00:37:02.470 --> 00:37:04.472
<i>♪ Pick it up. it was just for me ♪</i>

623
00:37:04.555 --> 00:37:06.515
-[all gasping]
<i>-♪ Oh. oh. oh ♪</i>

624
00:37:06.599 --> 00:37:08.601
<i>♪ Lucky me ♪</i>

625
00:37:10.269 --> 00:37:12.021
<i>♪ My best friend is the one I love ♪</i>

626
00:37:12.104 --> 00:37:14.065
[Penny] The Commander's office
is down there.

627
00:37:14.148 --> 00:37:16.567
This is his wine cellar.

628
00:37:17.777 --> 00:37:20.905
He's got a Domaine Romanée-Conti
from 1945.

629
00:37:20.988 --> 00:37:21.989
[Hulda] What's that?

630
00:37:22.073 --> 00:37:23.824
[Shunammite] Burgundy. Very rare.

631
00:37:23.908 --> 00:37:26.702
<i>♪ I just want a laugh</i>
<i>with a cherry on top ♪</i>

632
00:37:27.370 --> 00:37:30.998
[Penny] <i>We have plans to build</i>
<i>the nursery next to our room.</i>

633
00:37:31.082 --> 00:37:32.708
I've. um...

634
00:37:32.792 --> 00:37:34.877
<i>♪ Bum. bum. ba-dum-bum ♪</i>

635
00:37:34.961 --> 00:37:37.171
I've been feeling ill
the past few mornings.

636
00:37:38.172 --> 00:37:41.592
It's in God's hands.
but I pray it's a sign.

637
00:37:41.676 --> 00:37:45.888
-[Plums exclaiming]
-[Penny chuckles]

638
00:37:45.972 --> 00:37:48.224
[sighs] This way. come on.

639
00:37:48.307 --> 00:37:49.517
I chose these.

640
00:37:49.600 --> 00:37:50.810
This one.

641
00:37:50.893 --> 00:37:52.853
This one reminds me of my mother.

642
00:37:52.937 --> 00:37:54.772
<i>♪ Oh. oh. oh... ♪</i>

643
00:37:54.855 --> 00:37:56.190
Aren't they cute?

644
00:37:56.274 --> 00:37:57.483
Praise be.

645
00:37:59.277 --> 00:38:01.279
Now... [claps hands] who's hungry?

646
00:38:01.362 --> 00:38:03.364
<i>♪ Ah. ah. ah. ah ♪</i>

647
00:38:04.240 --> 00:38:07.743
<i>♪ We don't know the time we got ♪</i>

648
00:38:08.577 --> 00:38:11.330
<i>♪ Oh. I just want a laugh</i>
<i>with a cherry on top ♪</i>

649
00:38:11.414 --> 00:38:13.958
Bless us. O Lord. and these Thy gifts.

650
00:38:14.041 --> 00:38:17.211
which we are about to receive
from Thy bounty.

651
00:38:17.295 --> 00:38:18.504
[all] Amen.

652
00:38:20.840 --> 00:38:22.842
Your house is beautiful. Penny.

653
00:38:22.925 --> 00:38:24.552
[Penny] You should've seen it
when I moved in.

654
00:38:24.635 --> 00:38:26.846
Michael was up a decorating creek
without a paddle.

655
00:38:26.929 --> 00:38:28.806
-[polite laughter]
-Who's Michael?

656
00:38:28.889 --> 00:38:31.559
Commander Judd. Hulda. Don't be thick.

657
00:38:31.642 --> 00:38:34.228
I imagine it's a lot to handle.

658
00:38:34.312 --> 00:38:35.521
Being a new wife.

659
00:38:36.605 --> 00:38:37.940
[Penny] Some days.

660
00:38:38.024 --> 00:38:40.901
But God only sends us what we can bear.

661
00:38:40.985 --> 00:38:43.070
Well. I could bear this. [chuckles]

662
00:38:43.154 --> 00:38:44.989
[all chuckling]

663
00:38:45.072 --> 00:38:46.699
[footsteps approaching]

664
00:38:46.782 --> 00:38:48.993
[Commander Judd] Don't mind me.
I'm just passing through.

665
00:38:50.703 --> 00:38:51.996
This looks fun.

666
00:38:52.580 --> 00:38:55.583
[Penny] Don't tell on us. It's just cider.

667
00:38:56.292 --> 00:38:58.294
Your secret's safe with me.

668
00:38:58.794 --> 00:39:00.004
[kiss smacks]

669
00:39:03.132 --> 00:39:04.550
Welcome to our home.

670
00:39:04.633 --> 00:39:06.844
Thank you for having us. Commander. sir.

671
00:39:08.179 --> 00:39:11.182
You all showed the world
some Gilead grit last week.

672
00:39:12.683 --> 00:39:14.101
During that attack.

673
00:39:16.103 --> 00:39:18.439
I just hope you know
that they're just jealous.

674
00:39:18.522 --> 00:39:21.067
'Cause we have clean water.

675
00:39:21.150 --> 00:39:22.693
and fresh air.

676
00:39:22.777 --> 00:39:24.403
and fruitful young women.

677
00:39:25.529 --> 00:39:27.740
And they have pollution and hate.

678
00:39:30.368 --> 00:39:31.786
We love.

679
00:39:32.912 --> 00:39:36.916
We take in God's children.
wherever they come from.

680
00:39:40.127 --> 00:39:41.962
Blessed evening.

681
00:39:43.172 --> 00:39:44.799
Blessed evening. sir.

682
00:39:46.384 --> 00:39:48.386
Thanks so much for having us.

683
00:39:51.180 --> 00:39:53.391
I don't want to put you on the spot.

684
00:39:54.558 --> 00:39:57.061
I'm just curious why you decided
to come to Gilead.

685
00:40:00.231 --> 00:40:01.857
To serve God's will.

686
00:40:03.984 --> 00:40:04.985
Of course.

687
00:40:07.947 --> 00:40:09.949
And there was nothing left for me.

688
00:40:11.367 --> 00:40:12.368
[sighs]

689
00:40:13.202 --> 00:40:14.787
Well. you have a new home now.

690
00:40:16.539 --> 00:40:17.748
[softly chuckles]

691
00:40:20.543 --> 00:40:21.752
Praise be.

692
00:40:23.003 --> 00:40:26.006
[♪ ominous music playing]

693
00:40:31.554 --> 00:40:33.764
[utensils clanging]

694
00:40:42.022 --> 00:40:43.858
-I'm so happy for you.
-Here you are. Aunt Vidala.

695
00:40:43.941 --> 00:40:45.943
[group quietly chattering]

696
00:40:49.989 --> 00:40:51.991
[Daisy]
<i>The Pearl Girl program was designed</i>

697
00:40:52.074 --> 00:40:54.285
<i>to wash away our sins for God.</i>

698
00:40:55.703 --> 00:40:57.538
<i>To let us start anew.</i>

699
00:40:59.248 --> 00:41:01.250
<i>But I was never really a Pearl Girl.</i>

700
00:41:02.543 --> 00:41:03.961
<i>You know that by now.</i>

701
00:41:08.382 --> 00:41:10.217
[whispering] What the fuck happened?

702
00:41:10.301 --> 00:41:12.344
Was that us? Was that Mayday?

703
00:41:16.182 --> 00:41:17.766
That's what Gilead's saying.

704
00:41:17.850 --> 00:41:19.477
What do your contacts say?

705
00:41:20.728 --> 00:41:22.563
It was meant to be a retrieval mission.

706
00:41:23.189 --> 00:41:24.815
Retrieval?

707
00:41:24.899 --> 00:41:27.067
Like. kidnapping?

708
00:41:27.151 --> 00:41:29.361
Jesus fucking Christ.

709
00:41:30.446 --> 00:41:32.072
[dog barking]

710
00:41:32.740 --> 00:41:34.366
[Garth] What is this?

711
00:41:34.992 --> 00:41:37.703
[Daisy] Map of the school.
You're welcome.

712
00:41:39.497 --> 00:41:40.915
[chuckles slightly]

713
00:41:40.998 --> 00:41:42.541
[paper crinkling]

714
00:41:42.625 --> 00:41:44.210
This is good.

715
00:41:44.293 --> 00:41:45.711
[Daisy] Where's it going?

716
00:41:46.670 --> 00:41:49.006
It's not gonna be used
to hurt those girls. is it?

717
00:41:50.966 --> 00:41:52.593
The girls weren't supposed to get hurt.

718
00:41:53.344 --> 00:41:54.720
That's not comforting.

719
00:41:54.803 --> 00:41:57.848
to know that you guys
are just some sloppy shitshow.

720
00:41:58.516 --> 00:42:03.604
My life is in your hands here.
for fuck's sake.

721
00:42:03.687 --> 00:42:04.772
[door opening]

722
00:42:05.898 --> 00:42:08.108
[Plums chattering]

723
00:42:14.448 --> 00:42:16.075
I need to speak to June.

724
00:42:17.826 --> 00:42:19.036
Who's June?

725
00:42:19.119 --> 00:42:21.121
[approaching footsteps]

726
00:42:26.502 --> 00:42:29.505
-[bell tolling]
-[plate grinding]

727
00:42:39.723 --> 00:42:40.766
Do you want anything else?

728
00:42:40.849 --> 00:42:41.850
No.

729
00:42:44.270 --> 00:42:45.354
Thank you.

730
00:42:49.567 --> 00:42:51.986
So. Gilead killed Neil and Melanie?

731
00:42:52.069 --> 00:42:53.612
Mm-hmm.

732
00:42:53.696 --> 00:42:56.073
Because they were working with Mayday?

733
00:42:57.700 --> 00:42:58.784
Mm-hmm.

734
00:42:59.326 --> 00:43:01.537
So. why does Gilead give a shit about me?

735
00:43:02.413 --> 00:43:04.415
Why does Gilead want to kill me?

736
00:43:05.040 --> 00:43:06.667
They don't want to kill you.

737
00:43:07.793 --> 00:43:09.628
They want to take you back.

738
00:43:10.296 --> 00:43:12.506
They want to take you back to Gilead.

739
00:43:13.215 --> 00:43:14.633
Why?

740
00:43:16.719 --> 00:43:19.138
Because they think you belong to them.

741
00:43:20.889 --> 00:43:22.516
Because you got away.

742
00:43:25.894 --> 00:43:29.440
Your parents. in Gilead.

743
00:43:29.523 --> 00:43:31.734
got you out when you were a baby.

744
00:43:32.526 --> 00:43:35.738
Neil and Melanie
have never been to Gilead.

745
00:43:35.821 --> 00:43:37.239
[sighs]

746
00:43:37.823 --> 00:43:39.450
[softly] That's right. Daisy.

747
00:43:47.875 --> 00:43:49.460
When you got out of Gilead.

748
00:43:49.543 --> 00:43:52.004
they would not stop looking for you.

749
00:43:53.255 --> 00:43:55.257
And they were never gonna let you go.

750
00:43:56.216 --> 00:43:57.843
So. we had to get you to safety.

751
00:43:57.926 --> 00:44:01.764
and Neil and Melanie... took you in.

752
00:44:02.598 --> 00:44:03.599
No way.

753
00:44:05.768 --> 00:44:07.102
I would have known.

754
00:44:07.186 --> 00:44:08.729
[sighs heavily]

755
00:44:08.812 --> 00:44:10.981
My parents were
the shittiest liars in the world.

756
00:44:11.065 --> 00:44:13.400
I would have known...

757
00:44:13.484 --> 00:44:15.319
if I wasn't really theirs.

758
00:44:17.237 --> 00:44:18.864
You were theirs.

759
00:44:24.828 --> 00:44:26.455
[breathing deeply]

760
00:44:27.122 --> 00:44:28.832
When you first got out of Gilead...

761
00:44:31.168 --> 00:44:34.296
you would not stop screaming.

762
00:44:34.380 --> 00:44:37.633
-Hm.
-Oh. my God. [chuckles]

763
00:44:37.716 --> 00:44:40.719
You were just-- You were so--
You were so little.

764
00:44:43.472 --> 00:44:45.974
And Mayday took you to Neil and Melanie

765
00:44:46.058 --> 00:44:48.060
in the middle of the night.

766
00:44:48.894 --> 00:44:51.105
And they had no idea
you were coming. you know?

767
00:44:51.188 --> 00:44:53.399
So they didn't have any diapers.

768
00:44:53.482 --> 00:44:55.109
or a crib.

769
00:44:55.192 --> 00:44:57.861
or any food for you to eat.

770
00:44:57.945 --> 00:44:59.279
They didn't--

771
00:44:59.363 --> 00:45:01.990
They'd never had a baby
of their own. you know?

772
00:45:02.658 --> 00:45:07.204
So. Neil went to the store...

773
00:45:07.287 --> 00:45:09.498
and Melanie started singing to you.

774
00:45:11.333 --> 00:45:13.168
But you would have none of it.

775
00:45:14.211 --> 00:45:15.963
You just--

776
00:45:16.046 --> 00:45:18.966
Nope. just cried and cried.

777
00:45:19.425 --> 00:45:22.845
But Melanie kept singing
and singing and...

778
00:45:24.972 --> 00:45:26.390
She sang you show tunes.

779
00:45:26.473 --> 00:45:28.892
[both chuckle]

780
00:45:29.852 --> 00:45:33.856
For hours. 'til you finally went to sleep.

781
00:45:37.192 --> 00:45:39.611
[whispering] She couldn't believe
how strong you were.

782
00:45:42.114 --> 00:45:43.949
How do you know that?

783
00:45:44.032 --> 00:45:46.160
It was Melanie's favorite story.

784
00:45:46.243 --> 00:45:49.079
[chuckles] She told it to me
dozens of times.

785
00:45:49.163 --> 00:45:52.416
The story of how you came to them.

786
00:45:54.585 --> 00:45:56.754
"It's like <i>Harry Potter." </i>she said.

787
00:46:02.634 --> 00:46:04.553
Daisy... [inhales]

788
00:46:06.930 --> 00:46:08.557
...you were theirs.

789
00:46:11.185 --> 00:46:13.187
In all the ways that matter.

790
00:46:16.064 --> 00:46:17.566
And they died because of me.

791
00:46:17.649 --> 00:46:19.485
-No.
-Mm-hmm.

792
00:46:20.736 --> 00:46:21.737
No.

793
00:46:22.529 --> 00:46:25.365
Gilead killed them. Okay?

794
00:46:27.242 --> 00:46:30.954
Listen to me.
You are not responsible for that.

795
00:46:32.915 --> 00:46:36.668
You know. just because
you say it with conviction.

796
00:46:36.752 --> 00:46:38.587
doesn't make it not bullshit.

797
00:46:43.300 --> 00:46:48.055
Just... don't start doing that
to yourself. okay?

798
00:46:48.138 --> 00:46:50.808
That kind of thinking's
really gonna fuck you up.

799
00:46:50.891 --> 00:46:52.559
Do you understand me? [sniffles]

800
00:46:52.643 --> 00:46:54.061
Not really.

801
00:46:58.857 --> 00:47:00.067
Wait. where are you going?

802
00:47:00.150 --> 00:47:03.278
Stay here. Just keep ordering coffee.

803
00:47:03.362 --> 00:47:04.863
Someone's gonna come get you.

804
00:47:04.947 --> 00:47:06.573
You're leaving me alone?

805
00:47:06.657 --> 00:47:09.284
[♪ gentle music playing]

806
00:47:10.118 --> 00:47:13.121
You are never alone.

807
00:47:15.040 --> 00:47:16.667
Mayday's got you.

808
00:47:18.126 --> 00:47:20.128
We've always had you.

809
00:47:23.507 --> 00:47:25.342
From the beginning.

810
00:47:29.763 --> 00:47:31.932
Don't let the bastards
grind you down. okay?

811
00:47:32.349 --> 00:47:33.350
Okay.

812
00:47:34.893 --> 00:47:37.521
Sure. I won't let them.

813
00:47:40.858 --> 00:47:43.861
[♪ gentle. melancholy music playing]

814
00:47:51.702 --> 00:47:54.329
-[metro train rumbling]
-[bell rings]

815
00:48:03.255 --> 00:48:05.257
♪♪

816
00:48:15.475 --> 00:48:17.477
[money rustling]

817
00:48:25.611 --> 00:48:27.613
♪♪

818
00:49:44.690 --> 00:49:46.692
[insects chirring]

819
00:49:48.694 --> 00:49:50.696
[rooster crowing]

820
00:49:52.698 --> 00:49:54.700
[roaring]
